The paper deals with distance labeling schemes for graphs, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and graph theory (cs.DM), as well as computational geometry (cs.CG) for some of the geometric aspects of the problem. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed labeling schemes in network infrastructure (cs.NI).
